import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of component sizes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_size_by_parent = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='parent', y='size', data=avg_size_by_parent)
    plt.title('What is the average size of software components?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=480, height=480).generate(text)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of component names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
